# CI/CD and Pre-commit Integration

## Pre-commit Hooks Setup
For optimal rule enforcement, configure these pre-commit hooks:

```bash
# Install husky for git hooks
pnpm add -D husky

# Add pre-commit script to package.json
{
  "scripts": {
    "pre-commit": "pnpm lint && pnpm type-check"
  }
}
```

## Vercel Build Configuration
Ensure these build steps are included in deployment:

```javascript
// next.config.mjs
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  eslint: {
    // Don't ignore ESLint errors during build
    ignoreDuringBuilds: false,
  },
  typescript: {
    // Don't ignore TypeScript errors during build
    ignoreBuildErrors: false,
  },
}
```

## GitHub Actions Integration
For automatic rule validation, add `.github/workflows/validate.yml`:

```yaml
name: Validate Code Quality
on: [push, pull_request]
jobs:
  validate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
        with:
          node-version: '18'
      - run: pnpm install
      - run: pnpm lint
      - run: pnpm type-check
      - run: pnpm build
```

## Rule Validation Commands
Add these scripts to package.json for comprehensive validation:

```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "validate": "pnpm lint && pnpm type-check && pnpm build",
    "type-check": "tsc --noEmit",
    "lint:fix": "next lint --fix"
  }
}
```

## Automatic Rule Application
These rules will be automatically applied when:
- Creating new components or pages
- Modifying existing TypeScript/React code
- Adding new features or functionality
- Refactoring existing code
- Importing or using external libraries

## IDE Integration
Configure VS Code settings for automatic rule enforcement:

```json
{
  "editor.formatOnSave": true,
  "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
    "source.fixAll.eslint": true
  },
  "typescript.preferences.importModuleSpecifier": "non-relative"
}
```